body_html:
@satok16
I had written Android application for OnePlus 3T phone (This has snapdragon 821 and i have flashed my own compiled android image out of LineageOS, that means it completely rooted and /system is write accessible) but it was crashing and hence i tried following sample test for hexagon:

$ adb shell 'LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/data/local/tmp:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH' "/data/local/tmp/hexagon_graph_execution"
WARNING: linker: Warning: unable to normalize ""
Running main() from test_main.cc
[==========] Running 1 test from 1 test case.
[----------] Global test environment set-up.
[----------] 1 test from GraphTransferer
[ RUN      ] GraphTransferer.RunInceptionV3OnHexagonExampleWithTfRuntime
native : hexagon_graph_execution_test.cc:446 Fuse and run inception v3 on hexagon with tf runtime
tensorflow/core/kernels/hexagon/hexagon_graph_execution_test.cc:71: Failure
Expected: (version) >= (1), actual: 0 vs 1

The problem here is that the version is showing '0', does that mean DSP is not accessible?

UPDATE:
Verified logcat and getting consistent the error is following:

01-13 05:58:44.477 4373 4373 D adsprpc : vendor/qcom/proprietary/adsprpc/src/fastrpc_apps_user.c:437: dlopen error: hexagon_nn signature verify start failed for libhexagon_nn_skel.so

To avoid this, created testsig-xxxx but still it doesn't help much. Is there a workaround for this problem?

body:
@satok16 
I had written Android application for OnePlus 3T phone (This has snapdragon 821 and i have flashed my own compiled android image out of LineageOS, that means it completely rooted and /system is write accessible) but it was crashing and hence i tried following sample test for hexagon:

```
$ adb shell 'LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/data/local/tmp:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH' "/data/local/tmp/hexagon_graph_execution"
WARNING: linker: Warning: unable to normalize ""
Running main() from test_main.cc
[==========] Running 1 test from 1 test case.
[----------] Global test environment set-up.
[----------] 1 test from GraphTransferer
[ RUN      ] GraphTransferer.RunInceptionV3OnHexagonExampleWithTfRuntime
native : hexagon_graph_execution_test.cc:446 Fuse and run inception v3 on hexagon with tf runtime
tensorflow/core/kernels/hexagon/hexagon_graph_execution_test.cc:71: Failure
Expected: (version) >= (1), actual: 0 vs 1

```
The problem here is that the version is showing '0', does that mean DSP is not accessible? 

**UPDATE**:
Verified logcat and getting consistent the error is following:

`01-13 05:58:44.477  4373  4373 D adsprpc : vendor/qcom/proprietary/adsprpc/src/fastrpc_apps_user.c:437: dlopen error: hexagon_nn signature verify start failed for libhexagon_nn_skel.so`

To avoid this, created testsig-xxxx but still it doesn't help much. Is there a workaround for this problem?
